libroxml
------------------------------------------
This library is minimum, easy-to-use, C implementation for xml file parsing.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.6.5-1
  libroxml-devel-3.0.2-1bl2
  libroxml0-3.0.2-1bl2
  pkg-config-2.5.1-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  autoconf-15-2
  automake-20250528-1
  binutils-2.45.1-1
  cygport-0.37.5-1
  gcc-core-13.4.0-1
  libtool-2.5.4-1
  make-4.4.1-2

Canonical website:
  https://www.libroxml.net/

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/blunderer/libroxml/archive/refs/tags/3.0.2.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack libroxml-3.0.2-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./libroxml-3.0.2-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/libroxml-3.0.2-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libroxml-3.0.2-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libroxml0-3.0.2-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libroxml-devel-3.0.2-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(libroxml)
  /usr/bin/rocat.exe
  /usr/bin/roxml.exe
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/libroxml.README
  /usr/share/doc/libroxml/License.txt
  /usr/share/man/man1/roxml.1.gz

(libroxml0)
  /usr/bin/cygroxml-0.dll

(libroxml-devel)
  /usr/include/roxml.h
  /usr/lib/libroxml.dll.a
  /usr/lib/pkgconfig/libroxml.pc

------------------

